cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM

The paper focuses on the task of reconstructing 3D cities from historical images, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques such as image segmentation and inpainting. The resulting 3D models can be used for immersive experiences, which falls under graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of a novel architecture, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the goal of creating immersive historical experiences implies a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
